OPERATIONS PROCESS
A.	INTRODUCTION
This lesson provides an introduction to the Cyber Protection Team (CPT) Operations Process (OP). Cyber Warfare Publication (CWP) 3-33.4, Appendix A provides the basis for this course. Learn and review topics applicable to the CPT operations process. CPTs carry out set OPs to combat ongoing threats. These processes are an integral part to the full spectrum of Cyberspace Operations (CO).
Estimated time to complete: 2.0 hours

B.	ENABLING OBJECTIVES
Upon successful completion of this section, you will be able to:
2.1.1	Become familiar with policies, procedures, and regulations that govern Defensive Cyberspace Operations (DCO)
2.1.2	Become familiar with CWP 3-33.4, Appendix A
2.1.3	Learn the step-by-step OP

C.	TOPIC OUTLINE
•	Explain the CPT’s Operations Process
•	Discuss CWP 3-33.4, Appendix A

D.	TOOLKIT

