Data Collection Plan [See Job Sheet 2-2-3]
Conclusion
You have completed the Capability Analysis lesson. You used the Moodle platform to complete exercises that strengthened your understanding of Capability Analysis in the context of the CPT OP. You also learned about the mission capabilities provided by a CPT, and which scenarios they can be used in to fulfill mission requirements. Finally, you examined network locations, hosts, and the types of data that would provide answers to PIR.
You are now familiar with the capabilities analysis step of the CPT OP. You have the ability to identify which CPT core capabilities are appropriate given the mission requirements. You can create data collection plans which enable CPTs to efficiently gather intelligence to answer unknowns about your mission partner’s networks. These concepts and skills are essential in conducting CO in your role as a CDA on a CPT.
 
